{"word":"σκύλλω","slug":"σκύλλω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>σκύλλω</b></el> <el>(σκύλλω,) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to rend, mangle</i>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to trouble, annoy</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>vexare</el>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> or <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <el>μὴ σκύλλου</el> <i>trouble</i> not <i>thyself</i>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b>; <el>ἐσκυλμένοι</el> <i>troubled, distressed</i>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}